<header>
  <h1>Data Analytics Basics</h1>
  <p>A beginner's guide to understanding data analytics for students</p>
</header>

<div class="container">

  <section id="intro">
    <h2>📊 Why Data Analytics?</h2>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <h3>Why Should You Learn Data Analytics?</h3>
      <p>Data Analytics is a crucial skill for every student because:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Career Opportunities:</strong> High demand across industries with competitive salaries</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Decision Making:</strong> Learn to make data-driven decisions in any field</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Problem Solving:</strong> Develop critical thinking skills to solve complex problems</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Versatility:</strong> Applicable in business, healthcare, finance, marketing, and more</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="basics">
    <h2>📚 Data Analytics Basics</h2>
    
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Understanding Data Types</h3>
        <p>Start by learning these fundamental concepts:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><i class="fas fa-table"></i> <strong>Structured Data</strong> — Organized data in tables (spreadsheets, databases)</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> <strong>Unstructured Data</strong> — Text, images, videos without predefined format</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-chart-pie"></i> <strong>Quantitative vs. Qualitative</strong> — Numerical vs. descriptive data</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> <strong>Time Series</strong> — Data points collected over time intervals</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Data Analysis Process</h3>
        <p>Understand the key steps in analyzing data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> <strong>Data Cleaning</strong> — Handling missing values, outliers, and errors</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-random"></i> <strong>Data Transformation</strong> — Converting data into useful formats</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-search"></i> <strong>Exploratory Analysis</strong> — Finding patterns and relationships</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> <strong>Statistical Analysis</strong> — Applying statistical methods to draw conclusions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Data Visualization</h3>
        <p>Learn how to communicate insights effectively:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><i class="fas fa-chart-bar"></i> <strong>Chart Types</strong> — Bar, line, scatter plots, histograms, etc.</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-palette"></i> <strong>Design Principles</strong> — Color, layout, and accessibility</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i> <strong>Audience Focus</strong> — Tailoring visualizations to your audience</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-comment-dots"></i> <strong>Storytelling</strong> — Creating narratives with your data</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="tools">
    <h2>🛠️ Essential Tools</h2>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <h3>Tools Every Data Analyst Should Know</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><i class="fas fa-file-excel"></i> <strong>Excel/Google Sheets</strong> — Great starting point for data analysis</li>
        <li><i class="fab fa-python"></i> <strong>Python</strong> — With libraries like Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-database"></i> <strong>SQL</strong> — For querying and manipulating databases</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-chart-pie"></i> <strong>Tableau/Power BI</strong> — For creating interactive visualizations</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-code-branch"></i> <strong>R</strong> — Statistical programming language popular in academia</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="resources">
    <h2>🔗 Beginner-Friendly Resources</h2>
    <div class="resource-grid">
      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>DataCamp</h3>
        <p>Interactive courses covering Python, R, SQL, and data visualization with hands-on exercises.</p>
        <a href="https://www.datacamp.com/" target="_blank" class="btn">Explore</a>
      </div>

      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>Kaggle</h3>
        <p>Learn through competitions, datasets, notebooks, and courses while building a portfolio.</p>
        <a href="https://www.kaggle.com/learn" target="_blank" class="btn">Start Learning</a>
      </div>

      <div class="resource-card">
        <h3>Google Data Analytics Certificate</h3>
        <p>Comprehensive program teaching job-ready skills with real-world case studies.</p>
        <a href="https://www.coursera.org/professional-certificates/google-data-analytics" target="_blank" class="btn">View Course</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
<br><br>
  <section id="next-steps">
    <h2> Practice Projects for Beginners</h2>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <h3>Start Building Your Portfolio</h3>
      <p>Try these beginner-friendly projects to apply what you've learned:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><i class="fas fa-shopping-cart"></i> <strong>Sales Analysis</strong> — Analyze sales data to identify trends and patterns</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-heartbeat"></i> <strong>Health Tracker</strong> — Analyze personal health data (steps, sleep, etc.)</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-film"></i> <strong>Movie Recommendation</strong> — Build a simple recommendation system</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> <strong>Stock Market Analysis</strong> — Analyze historical stock data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>For each project, focus on:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What question are you trying to answer?</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-broom"></i> How will you clean and prepare the data?</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-chart-bar"></i> What visualizations will best communicate your findings?</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> What actionable insights can you derive?</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="sample-systems">
    <h2>🔍 Real-World Applications to Study</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><i class="fas fa-store"></i> <strong>Retail Analytics</strong> — How do companies like Amazon use data to optimize inventory?</li>
      <li><i class="fas fa-ad"></i> <strong>Marketing Analytics</strong> — How do social media platforms target advertisements?</li>
      <li><i class="fas fa-hospital"></i> <strong>Healthcare Analytics</strong> — How is data used to improve patient outcomes?</li>
      <li><i class="fas fa-money-bill-wave"></i> <strong>Financial Analytics</strong> — How do banks detect fraudulent transactions?</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="career-paths">
    <h2>🚀 Career Paths in Data Analytics</h2>
    <div class="tech-card">
      <h3>Where Can Data Analytics Take You?</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> <strong>Data Analyst</strong> — Analyze data to help businesses make decisions</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-database"></i> <strong>Database Administrator</strong> — Manage and optimize databases</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> <strong>Data Scientist</strong> — Apply advanced statistics and machine learning</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-chart-pie"></i> <strong>Business Intelligence Analyst</strong> — Create dashboards and reports</li>
        <li><i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i> <strong>Data Engineer</strong> — Build data pipelines and infrastructure</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>✨ Remember: Good Data Analysis starts with asking the right questions. Let the data tell its story! 📊</p>
  </footer>

</div>

</body>
</html>